# Backend Java — Team Standards

Read `web-backend/CODING_STANDARDS.md` for full rules. Summary:

## Must
- Controller: orchestration only, return DTO, Swagger `@Operation` + `@StandardApiResponses`
- Service: interface + impl; Facade delegates; Handler = one use-case
- Shared logic: `@Component` in `{domain}/support/` (TenantAccessSupport, *LookupSupport, *Validator)
- Errors: `PosExceptions.*` or `PosException` subclasses — never raw RuntimeException
- Logs: `LogUtil.info/warn/error` — no private Logger in services
- Mapping: MapStruct with `PosMapperConfig` — no BaseMapper
- Tenant: `TenantAccessSupport` — no duplicated company checks
- DB schema: Liquibase changelog — ddl-auto validate only
- Max ~300 lines per service, ~200 per handler — split if larger

## Must NOT
- `extends AbstractXxxSupport` for shared deps (use composition)
- `BaseCrudService`, `BaseMapper`, `BaseController`
- Entity in API response
- Repository or business logic in controller
- Static business logic
- Manual SQL without changelog

## New feature order
DTO → Liquibase → Entity → Repository → Mapper → Support/Handler → Service → Controller → Test

## Reference implementations
- Facade: `ProductServiceImpl`, `SaleServiceImpl`
- Support: `TenantAccessSupport`, `ProductLookupSupport`
- Cache abstract (only approved): `AbstractPosCacheRefreshService`
